Updating files for SOCAT: gvco2, NCEP pressure

GVco2, Data is at
 http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/gmd/ccgg/mbl/data.php
downloading the "surface" reference type (save to file if displayed).
Make a new version of the script GVCO2_2017.jnl and follow the comments in that script.

NCEP data
https://www.esrl.noaa.gov/psd/data/gridded/data.ncep.reanalysis.surface.html
Follow the links to get Sea Level Pressure 4 times daily.
Put the new file in /home/data/socat/ncep_slp_data/
Update and run the script make_ncep_slp.jnl to refer to the current data.
Using the script check_ncep_slp.jnl, compare output from the annual files and the merged file.
Copy the local ncep_slp.nc to /home/data/socat/ncep_slp_data/ as well as tmap@xtra:socat/Datasets/data/

WOA Salinity.  Not updated regularly (monthly climatology).
https://www.nodc.noaa.gov/OC5/WOA05/woa05nc.html
We have it here,
 use "http://ferret.pmel.noaa.gov/pmel/thredds/dodsC/data/PMEL/WOA05nc/monthly/s0112an1.nc"


